Guaranteed 100% E-Bay free.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukayleigh88.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kayleigh88</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/20/01 8:42:08 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://communities.msn.ca/_Secure/0MAAAAAQRZJwobQ10JEgBEVnTf2fwE2ks75hF4L27KUCO9em3zq3LL6!q8Jf7rFgS2dffE3vlh*IEAAAAWBMRAw/kayleigh.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to hunt 29-34?</span><hr size=1> Generally quad-able mobs have lower hp for their level, do not resist much, and do not cast. I mention this because usually whatever you can quad you can also root dot a few levels before. Cougars are perfectly good for the 29 to 34 levels, especially if you have 181 wis.<br>
<br>
Kayleigh, level 54 druid, Tholuxe Paells<br>
