Guaranteed 100% E-Bay free.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usnatzie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snatzie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/29/01 12:57:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.goldenstaff.org/pics/Snatzie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to hunt 29-34?</span><hr size=1> Cougars are good even before 34.  The trick is fear dotting and the reason it is effective with the cougars is due to pathing.  Ensnare a cougar and kite to the  eastern beach.  The docks work best because the cats will walk the length of the docks and this gives you more room to refresh dots and/or take melee swipes.   After you get a feel for the pathing the cougars take when feared you will find other good spots.   Just before the cougar catches up with you, fear it.  It will start staggering out off the end off the dock (or just into the water if you aren't at docks.)  It's this pathing that makes this a fairly simple procedure.  Because there are no other cats in the water - your feared cougar will never bring back an add.<br>
<br>
Once the cougar is in the water, you will probably have to wait for the fear to break before you can refresh the dots.  Just time the next fear to hit just before the cougar gets into melee range.   Once the fear hits, refresh the dots.   Most of the time you are medding.<br>
<br>
Why is this better than root dotting?  Its arguable, but I like fear kiting because:<br>
<br>
1) fear costs 1/2 as much and casts faster.  This means its easier to get to land and/or recast.   <br>
2) because of (1) its pretty easy to keep multiple cats feared if you accidently aggro one on the way back to the beach and it won't eat your mana supply.<br>
3) you can get a tank partner to follow behind and take whacks at it (or follow it yourself and keep your melee skills up).  The tank will take no damage so you don't have to heal.  Also, the cats will reverse direction once hit, so you can keep a cat wandering up and down the docks without having to chase it in the water.<br>
4) While it doesn't have a damage component, it has the advantage that you can close in on your target without risk of getting attacked.<br>
<br>
After awhile it gets pretty easy and the cougars don't stand a chance.  <br>
